@node "pubplug" "AmiHunterpub.amirx"

@{b}What is AmiHunterpub@{ub}

  Well, if you are not familar with Public Plugins read KĻĻ guide.

Install:

  Open KĻĻ GUI go to plugins.
  Under Public add
  
  Command: Find  Script:amihunterpub.amirx

  Click add

  Click Save

  You're all set... Now the channel can access your amihunter, using:
  
     <command prefix>FIND <search text>

  The output is sent via notices to the user who requested it...

@endnode

@node "amihunter" "AmiHunter.amirx"

@{b}What is AmiHunter@{ub}

  What is AmiHunter? Well kinda a Cross between Aminetfind.amirx &      
  AmircFetch.amirx.  

  So really, what is AmiHunter? AmiHunter lets you search and download
  from aminet via Amirc. Aminetfind.amirx worked great for finding files,
  but didn't download. Amircfetch.amirx used ftpget to download and
  required you to type in the full path of file you wanted to download,
  and had no progress indicator of the file progess. So AmiHunter was born,
  Which Searches/Gets/Views Readme's of the requested files all in and has
  a download progress GUI.

  AmiHunter is EMailware and included in KuangĻĻ 3.0.

  Author's Email   : bosman@erols.com
   
  Author's Website : @{u}http://www.erols.com/bosman/@{uu}

                     @{"Send IBrowse" rxs "if show('P','IBROWSE') then do;address IBROWSE;'GOTOURL http://www.erols.com/bosman/';end"} @{"Send Voyager" rxs "if show('P','VOYAGER') then do;address VOYAGER;'OPENURL http://www.erols.com/bosman/';end"} @{" Send AWEB  " rxs "if show('P','AWEB.1') then do;address AWEB.1;'OPEN http://www.erols.com/bosman/';end"}

  Co-Author's Email: entity@zeelandnet.nl
    

@endnode

